  "root_text": {
    "kp7:0.1": "Khuddakapāṭha 7 ",
    "kp7:0.2": "Tirokuṭṭasutta ",
    "kp7:1.1": "Tirokuṭṭesu tiṭṭhanti, ",
    "kp7:1.2": "sandhisiṅghāṭakesu ca; ",
    "kp7:1.3": "Dvārabāhāsu tiṭṭhanti, ",
    "kp7:1.4": "āgantvāna sakaṁ gharaṁ. ",
    "kp7:2.1": "Pahūte annapānamhi, ",
    "kp7:2.2": "khajjabhojje upaṭṭhite; ",
    "kp7:2.3": "Na tesaṁ koci sarati, ",
    "kp7:2.4": "sattānaṁ kammapaccayā. ",
    "kp7:3.1": "Evaṁ dadanti ñātīnaṁ, ",
    "kp7:3.2": "ye honti anukampakā; ",
    "kp7:3.3": "Suciṁ paṇītaṁ kālena, ",
    "kp7:3.4": "kappiyaṁ pānabhojanaṁ. ",
    "kp7:4.1": "Idaṁ vo ñātīnaṁ hotu, ",
    "kp7:4.2": "sukhitā hontu ñātayo; ",
    "kp7:4.3": "Te ca tattha samāgantvā, ",
    "kp7:4.4": "ñātipetā samāgatā. ",
    "kp7:5.1": "Pahūte annapānamhi, ",
    "kp7:5.2": "sakkaccaṁ anumodare; ",
    "kp7:5.3": "Ciraṁ jīvantu no ñātī, ",
    "kp7:5.4": "yesaṁ hetu labhāmase. ",
    "kp7:6.1": "Amhākañca katā pūjā, ",
    "kp7:6.2": "dāyakā ca anipphalā; ",
    "kp7:6.3": "Na hi tattha kasī atthi, ",
    "kp7:6.4": "gorakkhettha na vijjati. ",
    "kp7:7.1": "Vaṇijjā tādisī natthi, ",
    "kp7:7.2": "hiraññena kayākayaṁ; ",
    "kp7:7.3": "Ito dinnena yāpenti, ",
    "kp7:7.4": "petā kālagatā tahiṁ. ",
    "kp7:8.1": "Unname udakaṁ vuṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "kp7:8.2": "yathā ninnaṁ pavattati; ",
    "kp7:8.3": "Evamevaṁ ito dinnaṁ, ",
    "kp7:8.4": "petānaṁ upakappati. ",
    "kp7:9.1": "Yathā vārivahā pūrā, ",
    "kp7:9.2": "paripūrenti sāgaraṁ; ",
    "kp7:9.3": "Evamevaṁ ito dinnaṁ, ",
    "kp7:9.4": "petānaṁ upakappati. ",
    "kp7:10.1": "Adāsi me akāsi me, ",
    "kp7:10.2": "ñāti mittā sakhā ca me; ",
    "kp7:10.3": "Petānaṁ dakkhiṇaṁ dajjā, ",
    "kp7:10.4": "pubbe katamanussaraṁ. ",
    "kp7:11.1": "Na hi ruṇṇaṁ vā soko vā, ",
    "kp7:11.2": "yā caññā paridevanā; ",
    "kp7:11.3": "Na taṁ petānamatthāya, ",
    "kp7:11.4": "evaṁ tiṭṭhanti ñātayo. ",
    "kp7:12.1": "Ayañca kho dakkhiṇā dinnā, ",
    "kp7:12.2": "saṅghamhi suppatiṭṭhitā; ",
    "kp7:12.3": "Dīgharattaṁ hitāyassa, ",
    "kp7:12.4": "ṭhānaso upakappati. ",
    "kp7:13.1": "So ñātidhammo ca ayaṁ nidassito, ",
    "kp7:13.2": "Petāna pūjā ca katā uḷārā; ",
    "kp7:13.3": "Balañca bhikkhūnamanuppadinnaṁ, ",
    "kp7:13.4": "Tumhehi puññaṁ pasutaṁ anappakanti. ",
    "kp7:14.1": "Tirokuṭṭasuttaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "kp7:0.1": "Basic Passages 7 ",
    "kp7:0.2": "Outside the Walls ",
    "kp7:1.1": "Outside the walls they stand and wait, ",
    "kp7:1.2": "at the junctions and the crossroads. ",
    "kp7:1.3": "Returning to their former homes ",
    "kp7:1.4": "they wait beside the door posts. ",
    "kp7:2.1": "But when lavish food and drink ",
    "kp7:2.2": "of many kinds is set out, ",
    "kp7:2.3": "no-one remembers them at all, ",
    "kp7:2.4": "because of those beings’s deeds. ",
    "kp7:3.1": "That’s why those who have compassion ",
    "kp7:3.2": "give to their relatives ",
    "kp7:3.3": "food and drink at the right time, ",
    "kp7:3.4": "that’s clean, delicious, and suitable. ",
    "kp7:4.1": "“May this be for our relatives! ",
    "kp7:4.2": "May our relatives be happy!” ",
    "kp7:4.3": "Those ghosts who have gathered there, ",
    "kp7:4.4": "the departed relatives who have come ",
    "kp7:5.1": "for the lavish food and drink ",
    "kp7:5.2": "gratefully express appreciation: ",
    "kp7:5.3": "“May our relatives live long! ",
    "kp7:5.4": "For those to whom we owe this gain, ",
    "kp7:6.1": "who have given honor to us, ",
    "kp7:6.2": "it will not be fruitless for the donor.” ",
    "kp7:6.3": "There is no farming there, ",
    "kp7:6.4": "no cow pasture can be found; ",
    "kp7:7.1": "likewise there’s no trading, ",
    "kp7:7.2": "and no commerce in gold coin. ",
    "kp7:7.3": "The departed, the dead in that place ",
    "kp7:7.4": "live on what is given here. ",
    "kp7:8.1": "Just as water that rains on high ",
    "kp7:8.2": "flows down to the plains, ",
    "kp7:8.3": "so too what is given here ",
    "kp7:8.4": "aids the departed ghosts. ",
    "kp7:9.1": "Just as the rivers full ",
    "kp7:9.2": "swell the ocean seas ",
    "kp7:9.3": "so too what is given here ",
    "kp7:9.4": "aids the departed ghosts. ",
    "kp7:10.1": "Thinking: “They gave to me, they did for me, ",
    "kp7:10.2": "they were my family, friend, comrade”, ",
    "kp7:10.3": "give offerings to departed kin, ",
    "kp7:10.4": "remembering past deeds. ",
    "kp7:11.1": "For neither tears nor grief ",
    "kp7:11.2": "or other lamentations ",
    "kp7:11.3": "are of any use to the departed, ",
    "kp7:11.4": "so long as their relatives stay like this. ",
    "kp7:12.1": "This offering that has been given, ",
    "kp7:12.2": "well placed in the Saṅgha, ",
    "kp7:12.3": "is for their lasting welfare, ",
    "kp7:12.4": "and aids them right away. ",
    "kp7:13.1": "The relative’s duty has now been shown: ",
    "kp7:13.2": "how high honor to departed is performed, ",
    "kp7:13.3": "how the mendicants can be kept strong, ",
    "kp7:13.4": "and how no little merit is produced by you. "
  },
